headshotImage.longCaption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: short into the body and Williams pulls it to fine leg as Zimbabwe level the series

commentPostTextItems.html: Join us for the final ODI on Wednesday at 9 am local time, 1 pm Bangladesh time. Abhishek Purohit signing off. Cheers

Sean Williams is the Man of the Match. Williams: "I am ecstatic. It was tough to lose a few wickets, kept my composure till the end. It was a fantastic batting deck. It was tough to bowl on this wicket."

Brendan Taylor: "Extremely happy with the guys. Williams was fantastic, Vusi set the tone for us and Waller finished it off. We held our nerve at the end. It will be a good game [the deciding ODI], the team that does not panic will get over the line. We need to show character."

Mushfiqur Rahim: "We did not bat well, couple of guys getting starts but not scoring big. 270-280 was a better total. One stage we were looking at 180 all out, but all credit to Razzak. We took a few wickets, did not bowl well througout."

This has been such a well-timed chase, set up by Vusi Sibanda's assault at the top. There were a few wobbles but what a calm hand by Sean Williams, supported by Malcolm Waller. It would have been a stunned Zimbabwe dressing room during the break after Razzak's blitz. But they themselves came out blazing, and that set the tone

Waller: "That was most needed to make it 1-1. It was important I had a good partnership with Willie. Struggled a bit but we did it. Guys were not too happy with the last two or three overs, we were looking at 220. But even 250 was about par on this wicket."

commentTextItems.html: bouncer around off, he had a look and decided to pull out in the end

commentPreTextItems.html: seansie: "Zim win...now i can turn off my speed dial to the ambulance(heart attack fears are always close by when my team plays) NOT TODAY!"

commentTextItems.html: swats a full toss to the deep cover boundary, the team scores are level, and this is also Sean Williams' highest ODI score
squeezes this full ball past the bowler to mid off
Waller had given up, he'd pushed to the off side and set off for the single, cover put in the dive, Waller had no chance of getting back, but the throw misses
slow, loopy full toss, he comes forward, eases it to sweeper cover and keeps strike

dismissalText.commentary: Shafiul Islam run out (Jarvis/SW Masakadza) 4 (6b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: what a fortuitous run out in the end, Razzak squeezed a push to short third man, before he knew it, Shafiul had charged across to his end, the throw came in on the bounce to the bowler, and ricocheted into the stumps off Shingi's thigh as he missed the take

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza b Shafiul Islam 15 (15b 3x4 0x6 20m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: he's gone through him, full and straight on off from Shafiul, Masakadza's played all around it, trying to hit it to leg and lost his off stump

dismissalText.commentary: Vusi Sibanda lbw b Shakib Al Hasan 49 (51b 7x4 0x6 67m) SR: 96.07

dismissalComment.html: he's been given after a long appeal, another start not quite converted by Sibanda, goes down on the knee for the sweep, misses, this pitches around middle and hits in front of middle and leg

dismissalText.long: c Shakib Al Hasan b Shafiul Islam
dismissalText.commentary: Sikandar Raza c Shakib Al Hasan b Shafiul Islam 23 (36b 3x4 0x6 48m) SR: 63.88

dismissalComment.html: soft dismissal, Raza's been moving across regularly to work to leg, and this time he's chipped it tamely to midwicket
